Interface Translatable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Circle, ComplexShape, Ellipse, Parallelogram, Rectangle, Rhombus, SimpleShape, Square, Trapezoid, Triangle

    public interface Translatable
    [Translatable.java] The interface translatable refers to all shapes that are able to translate on the grid. Both simple shapes and complex shapes implement this interface, but offer different methods to translate the shapes.
    Version:
    1.0, Oct 9, 2020
    Author:
    Braydon Wang

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void translate(int horizontal, int vertical)
      This method acts us the blueprint for all classes that implement the Translatable interface.

    • Method Detail

      • translate

        void translate(int horizontal,
               int vertical)
        This method acts us the blueprint for all classes that implement the Translatable interface. They must override this method with their own code.
        Parameters:
        horizontal - the horizontal shift applied to the shape
        vertical - the vertical shift applies to the shape
